TI  - Tubewell Solarization: A Step toward Climate-Resilient Agriculture in Pakistan
T2  - PAKISTAN JOURNAL OF AGRICULTURAL SCIENCES
LA  - English
KW  - High-efficiency irrigation systems
KW  - solar-powered tubewells
KW  - public policy framework
KW  - climate resilience
KW  - climate smart agriculture
AB  - Climate Change has profound global impacts, disproportionately affecting developing countries. This impact is evident across multiple sectors including agriculture-a cornerstone of many developing economies. Despite the agriculture sector contributing 24 % to GDP and 37.4% employment in FY 2023-24, Pakistan lags in adopting climate-resilient agricultural mechanization, and solar-powered High-Efficiency Irrigation Systems (HEIS). The use of tubewells has enhanced agricultural productivity, but it has deepened dependence on fossil fuels. Transitioning to solar-powered tubewells, while ensuring water availability and resource conservation, could mitigate environmental impacts and advance Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). This study examines tubewell solarization as a climate change policy intervention as well as a strategic agricultural technology that highlights its implications for irrigation efficiency, crop productivity, energy use, and farmer's response to climate variability. Based on the available literature and established policy analysis approaches this study has developed an integrated policy analysis framework to study the climate policy implementation in agriculture sector. An analysis of policy implementation challenges and the adoption of sustainable solar irrigation in Pakistan's agriculture sector identifies the predominance of diesel-powered tubewells in the irrigation system and highlights the associated economic and environmental challenges of fossil fuel dependency. Solar-powered tubewells present an opportunity to reduce operational costs and improve environmental outcomes; however, they raise concerns about potential groundwater over-extraction. This necessitates the need for regulatory measures to ensure sustainable water use. Findings of this study indicate that successful solarization of tubewells in Pakistan's agriculture sector hinges on comprehensive strategies addressing financial, technical, and institutional challenges beyond existing subsidies. This analytical review advocates integrated policy interventions and support mechanisms to achieve the sustainable development goals and policy deliverables outlined in Pakistan's National Climate Change Policy (2021).
