FX  - In this study we used data from the Pathways to Resilience in Semi-arid Economies (PRISE) research project supported by the UK Department for International Development (DFID) and the International Development Research Centre (IDRC) in Canada as part of the Collaborative Adaptation Research Initiative in Africa and Asia (CARIAA). We extend heartfelt appreciation to all PRISE research staff in Burkina Faso for their invaluable support. We are thankful to Professors Omer Combary (University Thomas Sankara) and Joshua Lewis (University of Montreal) for their guidance throughout the research process. The views expressed in this paper are solely ours and do not necessarily represent the views of DFID, IDRC or its Board of Governors. We also thank the editor and anonymous reviewers for the constructive comments.
